zdG1lbnQtYmFuay1pbi10b3AtZGVhbHMteWVhcg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB56e6b6c0" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Yeesh</a>=
:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s a scene playing =
out from New York to Sydney as Credit Suisse struggles to retain its most t=
alented advisers and risks losing out on valuable deals in one of the hotte=
st merger markets in years. More than 40 managing directors across the deal=
making side of the business have left since a pair of scandals rocked the f=
irm=E2=80=99s profits and image, including the M&amp;A chief and five globa=
l heads or co-heads of industry teams.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The =
departures have especially hit groups courting financial institutions and t=
echnology, media and telecom companies, two areas of traditional strength f=
or Credit Suisse. And of the 10 senior bankers the firm tapped late last ye=
ar for an elite squad to work on the biggest transactions across industries=
, three have left in recent months.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Many to=
p bankers are concerned about pay after the collapse of Archegos Capital Ma=
nagement cost the bank $5.5 billion. They also fret about the firm=E2=80=99=
s reputation after it angered asset management clients who had invested in =
now-frozen funds the bank offered with failed lender Greensill Capital. Cre=
dit Suisse has handed out some retention bonuses to keep top performers, bu=
t it hasn=E2=80=99t halted the stream of departures.</p></blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The real lesson here is that it is important for a b=
ank not to make=C2=A0<em>idiosyncratically=C2=A0</em>bad trades. In 2007 an=
d 2008, investment bankers had had a long run of doing tons of deals and ma=
king lots of money for their banks; also, though, mortgage traders lost a b=
ajillion dollars for those banks. That was very bad for the traders=E2=80=
=99 bonuses, and also quite bad for the investment bankers=E2=80=99 bonuses=
 and of course for everyone=E2=80=99s reputation with clients. The M&amp;A =
investment bankers, who were=C2=A0doing deals and serving clients and not s=
ecuritizing mortgages or destroying the financial system, had good reason t=
o be mad at their trader colleagues. But the investment bankers=C2=A0<em>ha=
d nowhere to go:=C2=A0</em>Every big bank was in roughly the same boat; bon=
uses were down everywhere. (The investment bankers=C2=A0could go to boutiqu=
es, which mostly hadn=E2=80=99t blown up on mortgage-backed finance;=C2=A0s=
ome of them did leave for boutiques, but the global financial crisis was ba=
d for M&amp;A, which limited the appeal of this too.)</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">On the other hand, when Archegos blew up, most of its banks mana=
ged to get out with minimal damage; Credit Suisse Group AG did not. And whe=
n Greensill blew up, Credit Suisse funds were big investors in its business=
; other banks=E2=80=99 funds were not. Investment banking everywhere else i=
s great! In fact, it is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/24569402.275148/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzL=
zIwMjEtMDctMTIvd2FsbC1zdHJlZXQtZGVhbG1ha2Vycy1zdGVwLWludG8tbGltZWxpZ2h0LXdp=
dGgtd2luZGZhbGwtbmVhcmluZw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9182c5f1" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> keeping up banks=E2=80=
=99 profits</a> in the face of declining trading revenue. The whole point o=
f a universal bank is that your different businesses are hedges to each oth=
er; when trading is bad M&amp;A can pick up the slack, and vice versa. But =
when your trading business is uniquely bad the M&amp;A bankers just leave.<=
/p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" ce=
